The vessel was laden with a thousand litres of diesel, as well as hundreds of thousands Styrofoam containers. CAPE TOWN Firefighters have contained a blaze on board a ship at Cape Town harbour.The vessel was laden with a thousand litres of diesel, as well as hundreds of thousands Styrofoam containers. The fire broke out yesterday morning.No injuries have been reported.#ShipFire The ship, Verona Port Villa, is believed to have had 100 000 litres of diesel on board.Fire and rescue spokesperson Theo Layne says: Currently we have a total of 13 firefighting vehicles on the scene at the Cape Town harbour, where the fire is burning on the ship. Whilst it s still contained, the extinguishing of the fire has to be done carefully in order not to cause the ship to list. (Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)